Being a potato? Well, if we let our imagination run wild...

To be a potato is to live a quiet, humble life underground. You start as a tiny sprout, nestled in the soil, your world dim, earthy, and comforting. Rain filters down through the dirt, and you soak in nutrients through your roots. The sun, though far away, sends its warmth through the leaves above, giving you the energy to grow plump and starchy.

You don’t worry about the stock market, politics, or what’s trending on social media. Your days are slow and simple. You divide your time between resting in the soil and occasionally contemplating the meaning of existence—if potatoes did that sort of thing.

Eventually, a hand might pull you from your cozy bed of earth. Your journey could take you to a kitchen, a farm stand, or even become part of a hearty stew, a mountain of mashed potatoes, or crisp golden fries. You may not have a long post-harvest life, but you bring joy, comfort, and sustenance to people all over the world.

So, what’s it like to be a potato? Peaceful. Purposeful. And deliciously important. 🥔✨

