Being a potato would likely be a quiet existence! You'd spend your early days growing underground, nestled in soil. No worries about deadlines or social media—just gradually developing eyes (the sprout kind, not the seeing kind). Your biggest excitement might be when you're finally harvested and see daylight for the first time. Then perhaps you'd wonder about your future—will you become french fries, mashed potatoes, or star in a child's science project? It would be a simple life, but an important one in the grand scheme of things, as you'd provide nourishment to someone eventually.

